Description: multi-backend, multi-modal framework for AI agent development
 Avalan is a Python SDK and CLI for building and running AI agents and
 workflows across local and hosted models. It exposes two console commands,
 avalan and avl, and ships with the default extras enabled: agent, server,
 tool and vendors.
 .
 Heavyweight optional features (local inference, audio, vision, GPU/CUDA,
 Apple MLX) are not included in this package; install them with pip into a
 user-controlled virtualenv on top of the system install.
